  "name": "Bollinger CMO Mean Reversion Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm implements a mean-reverting trading strategy using Bollinger Bands and the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO). It enters long positions when the price crosses below the lower Bollinger Band and the CMO indicates oversold conditions, aiming to capitalize on price reversals.",
  "algorithm_type": "MeanReverting",
  "prompt": "Develop an expert-level MeanReverting trading algorithm in Python that operates on 15-minute bars. Use the Bollinger Bands (20-period SMA with \u00b12 standard deviations) combined with the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO, 14 periods). Entry: enter a long position when the close price crosses below the lower Bollinger Band and the CMO is below -50, signaling oversold conditions. Enter a short position when the close crosses above the upper Bollinger Band and the CMO is above +50, signaling overbought. Exit trades when the price reverts to the 20-period SMA or when the CMO crosses zero, whichever happens first. Include volume filter: only take trades if volume is above its 20-period moving average to confirm momentum strength. Implement position sizing based on recent volatility using the Average True Range (ATR, 14 periods) to adjust stop-loss distance. Provide pseudocode to clearly outline indicator calculations, entry/exit logic, volume filter, and volatility-based stops.",
